1
00:00:03,603 --> 00:00:08,541
VISITING ROOM ENTRANCE
TOKYO DETENTION HOUSE

2
00:00:22,489 --> 00:00:23,890
It's been a long time.

3
00:00:36,236 --> 00:00:37,470
Every month…

4
00:00:40,340 --> 00:00:42,409
you've been writing me letters.

5
00:00:45,011 --> 00:00:45,845
I have.

6
00:00:49,449 --> 00:00:50,784
Please stop.

7
00:00:59,893 --> 00:01:00,860
I want…

8
00:01:04,364 --> 00:01:05,398
to die quietly.

9
00:01:25,118 --> 00:01:26,419
We're done here.

10
00:01:45,805 --> 00:01:46,739
Excuse me.

11
00:01:46,806 --> 00:01:49,409
There was an error
in the visiting request form

12
00:01:49,476 --> 00:01:51,845
submitted by Akizumi
from our office earlier.

13
00:01:51,911 --> 00:01:54,614
He asked me to fix it up for him.
Mind if I do that?

14
00:01:55,748 --> 00:01:57,317
Mr. Akizumi?

15
00:01:59,519 --> 00:02:01,287
He was here to see Mr. Yusaku Shimizu?

16
00:02:01,354 --> 00:02:03,123
That's right. To see Mr. Shimizu.

17
00:02:03,189 --> 00:02:04,157
YUSAKU SHIMIZU

18
00:02:04,224 --> 00:02:07,093
Since the visit's already over,
there's no need for corrections.

19
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:09,262
I see. Thank you.

20
00:02:10,797 --> 00:02:16,736
Yusaku Shimizu…

21
00:02:16,803 --> 00:02:18,171
YUSAKU SHIMIZU

22
00:02:45,832 --> 00:02:47,000
Is it too hot?

23
00:02:48,001 --> 00:02:50,069
Well? Do you like this?

24
00:02:51,538 --> 00:02:55,108
There are currently 64 dogs here
at the facility.

25
00:02:55,675 --> 00:02:59,112
Do you know why these dogs were abandoned?

26
00:02:59,646 --> 00:03:01,915
Their owners found them
to be too much work,

27
00:03:01,981 --> 00:03:05,318
couldn't take them along to new homes,
or their kids got bored of them.

28
00:03:06,052 --> 00:03:08,188
All for people's selfish reasons.

29
00:03:12,125 --> 00:03:16,729
In Japan, about 14,000 dogs and cats
are euthanized every year.

30
00:03:17,764 --> 00:03:18,698
That many?

31
00:03:19,699 --> 00:03:22,869
Just like humans,
they don't get to pick their parents.

32
00:03:24,470 --> 00:03:25,405
True.

33
00:03:27,941 --> 00:03:30,410
This place has actually been around
for quite a while.

34
00:03:31,344 --> 00:03:33,513
We've been working hard
for quite some time now.

35
00:03:37,584 --> 00:03:38,751
This girl…

36
00:03:41,821 --> 00:03:43,289
That's Saya. She's over there.

37
00:03:43,890 --> 00:03:45,225
Good, Mame.

38
00:03:45,758 --> 00:03:48,728
By the way, this Golden Retriever, Cocoa,

39
00:03:48,795 --> 00:03:51,598
is the mother of Mame over there.

40
00:03:51,664 --> 00:03:53,800
Nice, Mame.

41
00:03:53,866 --> 00:03:54,968
Then…

42
00:03:55,768 --> 00:03:57,170
who's this woman?

43
00:03:58,137 --> 00:03:59,339
That's Ms. Momose.

44
00:04:00,006 --> 00:04:01,674
Where is she right now?

45
00:04:03,676 --> 00:04:05,678
She passed away a long time ago.

46
00:04:17,557 --> 00:04:18,558
YUSAKU SHIMIZU

47
00:04:24,197 --> 00:04:27,533
YUSAKU SHIMIZU SENTENCED TO DEATH
FOR ITOI FAMILY MURDERS

48
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:31,104
Sentenced to death for murders…

49
00:04:32,005 --> 00:04:35,241
<i>The incident took place in 2012,</i>

50
00:04:36,442 --> 00:04:38,011
<i>twelve years ago from now,</i>

51
00:04:38,511 --> 00:04:41,681
<i>in a residential area in Hanamigawa Ward,
Chiba City, Chiba Prefecture.</i>

52
00:04:42,215 --> 00:04:44,517
<i>Makoto Itoi, a 42-year-old office worker,</i>

53
00:04:45,018 --> 00:04:46,619
<i>his 38-year-old wife Eriko,</i>

54
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:50,556
<i>and their 9-year-old daughter Natsu
were murdered in their home.</i>

55
00:04:50,623 --> 00:04:52,425
<i>No money or valuables were taken,</i>

56
00:04:52,492 --> 00:04:55,428
<i>leading the police to investigate it
as an act of revenge.</i>

57
00:04:55,928 --> 00:04:58,464
<i>And Yusaku Shimizu,
Itoi's colleague, was arrested.</i>

58
00:04:59,165 --> 00:05:00,366
It really wasn't me.

59
00:05:00,433 --> 00:05:03,970
<i>Itoi and Shimizu had been colluding
to embezzle company funds.</i>

60
00:05:04,704 --> 00:05:06,806
<i>They had a dispute over this money,</i>

61
00:05:06,873 --> 00:05:08,908
<i>resulting in Shimizu murdering Itoi.</i>

62
00:05:08,975 --> 00:05:12,545
<i>Initially, Shimizu denied
committing the crime,</i>

63
00:05:12,612 --> 00:05:14,547
<i>but he later confessed his guilt.</i>

64
00:05:15,448 --> 00:05:18,718
<i>He then received a death sentence
in the first trial.</i>

65
00:05:18,785 --> 00:05:21,187
<i>The defense counsel
chose not to appeal the verdict,</i>

66
00:05:21,254 --> 00:05:22,789
<i>and the trial came to a close.</i>

67
00:05:25,591 --> 00:05:27,827
<i>This office was established
only five years ago.</i>

68
00:05:27,894 --> 00:05:30,196
And Mr. Akizumi
wasn't an attorney before that.

69
00:05:30,263 --> 00:05:31,631
What was he doing?

70
00:05:31,698 --> 00:05:32,699
He was a prosecutor.

71
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:35,101
Twelve years ago…

72
00:05:36,836 --> 00:05:39,138
Mr. Akizumi would've
still been a prosecutor.

73
00:05:41,374 --> 00:05:43,976
Why did he visit a death row inmate?

74
00:06:22,915 --> 00:06:24,117
Isn't that him?

75
00:06:27,086 --> 00:06:29,922
Masato Uno is a charismatic attorney.

76
00:06:38,598 --> 00:06:41,534
Do all attorneys stay
at such luxury hotels?

77
00:06:41,601 --> 00:06:42,969
Are you jealous?

78
00:06:49,609 --> 00:06:53,479
Curiously, he makes frequent trips
to a hotel for "business reasons."

79
00:06:53,546 --> 00:06:54,614
USES IT FOR "BUSINESS"

80
00:06:57,950 --> 00:07:00,219
<i>Maybe I should've gone too.</i>

81
00:07:00,853 --> 00:07:03,589
Don't worry. Mr. Akizumi trusts them too.

82
00:07:09,162 --> 00:07:10,730
-Excuse me.
-Excuse me.

83
00:07:12,698 --> 00:07:14,300
I left something in the lobby!

84
00:07:14,367 --> 00:07:16,169
Seriously? Let's head back then.

85
00:07:29,015 --> 00:07:31,317
So, that woman back there isn't involved?

86
00:07:34,053 --> 00:07:35,154
Oh, crap.

87
00:07:47,366 --> 00:07:48,434
What are you--

88
00:08:07,553 --> 00:08:10,556
If they don't come out
for over an hour, we'll know for sure.

89
00:08:10,623 --> 00:08:11,457
Yes.

90
00:08:12,124 --> 00:08:14,427
But I'll hit you in five seconds.

91
00:08:14,494 --> 00:08:15,361
Sorry!

92
00:08:17,763 --> 00:08:19,732
That's a pretty good angle.

93
00:08:19,799 --> 00:08:20,633
Well done.

94
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:21,534
Thanks.

95
00:08:22,735 --> 00:08:24,270
Good work.

96
00:08:24,337 --> 00:08:25,738
Ms. Shiraki, the rundown, please.

97
00:08:25,805 --> 00:08:26,639
Right.

98
00:08:27,673 --> 00:08:30,743
There's been a series of rape
in Chiba City, Chiba Prefecture.

99
00:08:30,810 --> 00:08:33,246
The first victim is Ms. Sena Moriya.

100
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:37,483
<i>Late one night, when she returned
to her home where she lived alone,</i>

101
00:08:37,550 --> 00:08:40,186
<i>a man trailing her
threatened her with a knife.</i>

102
00:08:41,153 --> 00:08:44,824
<i>The man was wearing a balaclava,
so she couldn't see his face.</i>

103
00:08:45,525 --> 00:08:48,861
The second victim is Ms. Kasumi Toyama.

104
00:08:48,928 --> 00:08:51,898
She was targeted in the same way.

105
00:08:51,964 --> 00:08:56,536
Both reported the incidents
to the police after some time had passed.

106
00:08:56,602 --> 00:09:00,373
Consequently, there's no evidence linking
to the culprit, like DNA.

107
00:09:00,439 --> 00:09:03,476
With no eyewitness accounts
or physical evidence,

108
00:09:03,543 --> 00:09:05,111
the investigation has been difficult.

109
00:09:05,177 --> 00:09:07,013
And on February 21st,

110
00:09:07,079 --> 00:09:08,848
the third incident occurred.

111
00:09:08,915 --> 00:09:11,751
The third victim is Ms. Eri Sendo.

112
00:09:16,088 --> 00:09:18,691
<i>She was also threatened
with a knife in the same way</i>

113
00:09:18,758 --> 00:09:20,526
<i>and nearly pulled into her apartment.</i>

114
00:09:27,867 --> 00:09:29,101
Please stop!

115
00:09:29,168 --> 00:09:32,071
<i>She fought back desperately,
causing the man's mask to come off.</i>

116
00:09:33,673 --> 00:09:35,975
<i>Panicked, the man fled the scene.</i>

117
00:09:39,879 --> 00:09:44,317
The prosecution suspected Mr. Reiji Kurusu
of being the man and indicted him.

118
00:09:44,383 --> 00:09:48,955
Kurusu was arrested on suspicion
of sexually assaulting three women

119
00:09:49,021 --> 00:09:50,489
within Chiba City.

120
00:09:50,556 --> 00:09:51,490
Chiba…

121
00:09:52,158 --> 00:09:53,359
Why this case?

122
00:09:53,426 --> 00:09:54,794
A high-profile case like this

123
00:09:54,860 --> 00:09:57,263
is the perfect chance
to get your name out there.

124
00:09:57,830 --> 00:09:59,565
By the way, Kurusu was found guilty

125
00:09:59,632 --> 00:10:02,268
of committing an indecent act
without consent a year ago.

126
00:10:02,335 --> 00:10:04,971
But in this case,
the only conclusive evidence

127
00:10:05,037 --> 00:10:07,440
is the eyewitness account
of the third incident.

128
00:10:07,506 --> 00:10:11,944
Upon questioning, he confessed
to the first and second incidents.

129
00:10:12,011 --> 00:10:12,979
He confessed?

130
00:10:13,045 --> 00:10:15,014
But he hasn't admitted to the third.

131
00:10:15,081 --> 00:10:16,415
I assume…

132
00:10:17,283 --> 00:10:19,485
this was on Attorney Uno's advice.

133
00:10:21,153 --> 00:10:21,988
So,

134
00:10:22,755 --> 00:10:25,925
you wanted to snatch this case
from Attorney Uno. That's why…

135
00:10:28,894 --> 00:10:32,064
If you see a tasty fruit,
you have to go and pluck it yourself.

136
00:10:33,366 --> 00:10:35,201
I'm happy for you.

137
00:10:35,901 --> 00:10:37,269
What should we have for lunch?

138
00:10:37,336 --> 00:10:38,871
I want <i>omurice</i>!

139
00:10:38,938 --> 00:10:40,006
-<i>Omurice</i>?
-Let's see.

140
00:10:40,072 --> 00:10:42,508
-What else?
-What about this one?

141
00:10:54,420 --> 00:10:55,254
Here you go.

142
00:11:00,893 --> 00:11:02,395
It won't fly away anymore.

143
00:11:02,461 --> 00:11:03,496
Thanks!

144
00:11:03,562 --> 00:11:05,364
-I'm so sorry.
-No worries.

145
00:11:09,602 --> 00:11:11,303
So cool!

146
00:11:16,676 --> 00:11:17,743
Thanks.

147
00:11:23,082 --> 00:11:23,916
What's on yours?

148
00:11:24,950 --> 00:11:26,485
Nothing.

149
00:11:26,552 --> 00:11:28,387
It's been a while, Mr. Uno.

150
00:11:29,388 --> 00:11:31,157
Mind if we have a little chat?

151
00:11:33,959 --> 00:11:34,960
What's this about?

152
00:11:36,028 --> 00:11:37,863
Do you want me to spell it out?

153
00:11:43,703 --> 00:11:45,371
So, you're the Akizumi.

154
00:11:46,272 --> 00:11:48,407
I don't know what this is about,
but not today.

155
00:11:48,474 --> 00:11:52,411
I understand Yua is enrolling
in a private elementary school next year.

156
00:11:53,312 --> 00:11:54,447
How do you know that?

157
00:11:55,548 --> 00:11:57,850
I have a very simple deal for you.

158
00:11:57,917 --> 00:11:59,385
If you accept it,

159
00:11:59,452 --> 00:12:02,021
you can protect both your job
and your family.

160
00:12:07,093 --> 00:12:10,329
Seriously, you attorneys are so willful.

161
00:12:10,396 --> 00:12:12,732
You say you'll do something,
then change your mind.

162
00:12:12,798 --> 00:12:15,534
Everyone's got
their own circumstances, after all.

163
00:12:16,168 --> 00:12:18,637
But still, you're lucky.

164
00:12:20,206 --> 00:12:23,175
I'll be handling your defense now,

165
00:12:23,242 --> 00:12:25,244
and I want to confirm something again.

166
00:12:26,045 --> 00:12:29,281
You were maintaining your innocence,

167
00:12:29,882 --> 00:12:32,118
so why did you confess?

168
00:12:33,085 --> 00:12:35,421
Because that attorney told me to.

169
00:12:35,488 --> 00:12:37,656
"If the interrogation drags on,
it'll work against us."

170
00:12:37,723 --> 00:12:39,525
"You can tell the truth in court."

171
00:12:41,961 --> 00:12:43,229
I see.

172
00:12:44,196 --> 00:12:45,498
Just to confirm,

173
00:12:46,265 --> 00:12:50,603
when the third incident occurred,
where were you?

174
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:55,174
I went to my regular bar after work
and then headed straight home to sleep.

175
00:12:55,241 --> 00:12:56,542
Anything to prove that?

176
00:12:56,609 --> 00:12:59,211
The last time I got arrested,
it was such a pain,

177
00:12:59,278 --> 00:13:00,913
so I turn off my phone when moving.

178
00:13:02,114 --> 00:13:03,115
Say,

179
00:13:03,716 --> 00:13:05,584
they don't have much evidence against me.

180
00:13:05,651 --> 00:13:07,720
Is it true
I'll be found innocent in the trial?

181
00:13:07,787 --> 00:13:09,155
Of course.

182
00:13:10,756 --> 00:13:14,794
I promise to secure an acquittal for you.

183
00:13:17,496 --> 00:13:20,566
Getting a confession from him
only to overturn it later.

184
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:23,135
What was Attorney Uno's strategy?

185
00:13:23,202 --> 00:13:24,203
He is the guard, Osawa.

186
00:13:24,270 --> 00:13:25,371
I'm Osawa.

187
00:13:25,437 --> 00:13:28,140
-Here are Mr. Kurata and Mr. Onishi.
-Ms. Shinomiya?

188
00:13:28,207 --> 00:13:29,041
This way, please.

189
00:13:30,242 --> 00:13:32,044
Are they the prefectural police?

190
00:13:32,778 --> 00:13:33,879
Why are they here?

191
00:13:48,527 --> 00:13:50,496
Has there been any change in the accused?

192
00:13:50,563 --> 00:13:52,698
None. He's carrying on without any issue.

193
00:13:53,365 --> 00:13:54,500
As you're probably aware,

194
00:13:54,567 --> 00:13:58,070
once we arrive at the investigation room,
we'll move the accused.

195
00:13:58,137 --> 00:13:59,505
Have a seat while you wait.

196
00:14:02,074 --> 00:14:04,376
Mobile phones aren't permitted for use.

197
00:14:05,010 --> 00:14:06,412
-So I'll hold onto them.
-Right.

198
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:24,330
I still don't understand
Mr. Uno's intention.

199
00:14:24,396 --> 00:14:26,866
Why did he make Kurusu
confess to the crime?

200
00:14:26,932 --> 00:14:29,568
If Kurusu was claiming innocence,
Mr. Uno could've told him

201
00:14:29,635 --> 00:14:31,470
to deny the accusation or remain silent.

202
00:14:31,537 --> 00:14:33,572
Defending him
would've been simpler that way.

203
00:14:33,639 --> 00:14:37,843
It's quite a stretch to have him say,
"I confessed, but it was a lie."

204
00:14:37,910 --> 00:14:40,246
It's also odd Mr. Uno didn't make him
confess to the third incident.

205
00:14:40,312 --> 00:14:43,883
If only Kurusu had his phone turned on,
he'd have had a straightforward alibi.

206
00:14:43,949 --> 00:14:46,518
Anyway, the eyewitness account
for the third incident,

207
00:14:46,585 --> 00:14:51,390
which is the conclusive evidence,
conflicts with Mr. Kurusu's account.

208
00:14:56,295 --> 00:14:57,997
Wait, where's Mr. Akizumi?

209
00:15:02,968 --> 00:15:04,203
Do you have an appointment?

210
00:15:07,506 --> 00:15:08,941
Despite facing that ordeal,

211
00:15:09,775 --> 00:15:11,410
you're still fulfilling your duties.

212
00:15:12,044 --> 00:15:14,480
Your resilience is remarkable.

213
00:15:14,546 --> 00:15:15,848
I'm impressed.

214
00:15:18,517 --> 00:15:19,885
Who are you?

215
00:15:20,953 --> 00:15:22,054
Mr. Kurusu…

216
00:15:22,821 --> 00:15:25,324
and I have been acquainted for some time.

217
00:15:25,391 --> 00:15:27,826
Could I speak with you later?

218
00:15:31,597 --> 00:15:33,198
My shift ends at 7 p.m.

219
00:15:43,442 --> 00:15:44,843
I'm heading home.

220
00:15:44,910 --> 00:15:46,345
-Good night.
-Good night.

221
00:16:06,131 --> 00:16:07,800
I've been waiting for you.

222
00:16:11,603 --> 00:16:13,706
You finished work an hour early.

223
00:16:17,142 --> 00:16:18,911
I've told the police everything.

224
00:16:19,545 --> 00:16:21,080
Ask them for details.

225
00:16:21,146 --> 00:16:22,848
My apologies.

226
00:16:22,915 --> 00:16:26,352
You see, a few aspects
of your testimony trouble me.

227
00:16:27,886 --> 00:16:29,521
-Who are you?
-May I ask a few questions?

228
00:16:32,191 --> 00:16:33,525
Keep it brief.

229
00:16:34,827 --> 00:16:36,295
On the day of the incident,

230
00:16:36,362 --> 00:16:38,864
<i>you were threatened with a knife.</i>

231
00:16:38,931 --> 00:16:41,233
<i>You fought back desperately,</i>

232
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:43,102
<i>and saw the man's face.</i>

233
00:16:44,269 --> 00:16:47,206
<i>The man panicked and fled the scene.</i>

234
00:16:48,007 --> 00:16:50,109
I hear that is your testimony.

235
00:16:50,175 --> 00:16:51,910
Is this correct?

236
00:16:51,977 --> 00:16:53,212
What about it?

237
00:16:53,278 --> 00:16:55,381
Were you acquainted with Mr. Kurusu?

238
00:16:55,447 --> 00:16:56,749
Ask him yourself.

239
00:16:56,815 --> 00:16:58,851
It's a minor detail,

240
00:16:58,917 --> 00:17:04,022
but there's a convenience store
just 13 steps from the crime scene.

241
00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:21,306
<i>When you were threatened with a knife</i>

242
00:17:21,373 --> 00:17:24,943
<i>in front of your apartment,
why didn't you rush into the store?</i>

243
00:17:25,844 --> 00:17:29,948
I was overwhelmed with panic
and couldn't think clearly.

244
00:17:30,015 --> 00:17:32,618
If you had shouted,
surely someone would have noticed.

245
00:17:33,185 --> 00:17:36,355
But no one has come forward
with such testimony yet.

246
00:17:38,857 --> 00:17:42,161
Two days later, you went to the police

247
00:17:42,227 --> 00:17:43,896
to submit a victim's report.

248
00:17:43,962 --> 00:17:48,067
Why didn't you report the crime
to the police right after it happened?

249
00:17:50,102 --> 00:17:50,936
Because--

250
00:17:51,003 --> 00:17:53,806
It's difficult to speak out
against sex crimes.

251
00:17:55,040 --> 00:17:56,575
You wouldn't understand.

252
00:17:56,642 --> 00:17:57,843
Can I go now?

253
00:18:04,083 --> 00:18:06,819
It appears Uno really did resign
from Kurusu's defense.

